  <h2>What is Generative AI?</h2>
  <p>
    Generative AI refers to artificial intelligence systems that can create new content—text, images, code, audio, and more—based on patterns learned from training data. Unlike traditional AI that classifies or predicts, generative AI produces original outputs that didn't exist before.
  </p>
  <p>
    The most prominent examples include Large Language Models (LLMs) like GPT-4, Claude, and LLaMA, which power applications from chatbots to document analysis. These models understand context, follow instructions, and generate human-like responses.
  </p>

  <h2>Enterprise Use Cases Delivering ROI</h2>

  <h3>1. Customer Service Automation</h3>
  <p>
    AI-powered chatbots and virtual assistants are handling increasing volumes of customer inquiries with high accuracy. Unlike rule-based bots, generative AI understands natural language, handles complex queries, and provides personalized responses.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>40-60% cost reduction</strong> in customer support operations</li>
    <li><strong>24/7 availability</strong> without staffing constraints</li>
    <li><strong>Consistent quality</strong> across all interactions</li>
    <li><strong>Seamless escalation</strong> to human agents when needed</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>2. Document Processing & Intelligence</h3>
  <p>
    Enterprises process millions of documents annually—contracts, invoices, reports, and compliance documents. Generative AI extracts information, summarizes content, and identifies key insights at scale.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Contract analysis:</strong> Extract key terms, identify risks, compare against templates</li>
    <li><strong>Invoice processing:</strong> Automated data extraction and validation</li>
    <li><strong>Compliance monitoring:</strong> Flag potential issues in regulatory documents</li>
    <li><strong>Research synthesis:</strong> Summarize lengthy reports and extract actionable insights</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>3. Content Generation & Marketing</h3>
  <p>
    Marketing teams are using AI to scale content production while maintaining brand voice. From blog posts to product descriptions to email campaigns, AI accelerates content creation 5-10x.
  </p>
