  </p>

  <h2>Implementation Best Practices</h2>

  <h3>Start with Clear Use Cases</h3>
  <p>
    Don't implement AI for AI's sake. Identify specific business problems where AI can deliver measurable value:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>What manual processes consume the most time?</li>
    <li>Where do bottlenecks slow down operations?</li>
    <li>What tasks require scaling beyond current capacity?</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Prioritize Data Security</h3>
  <p>
    Enterprise AI implementations require careful attention to data handling:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Private deployments:</strong> Run models on your infrastructure when handling sensitive data</li>
    <li><strong>Data governance:</strong> Establish clear policies on what data can be processed by AI</li>
    <li><strong>Compliance:</strong> Ensure AI usage meets regulatory requirements (HIPAA, GDPR, SOC 2)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Build Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)</h3>
  <p>
    RAG systems combine LLMs with your proprietary knowledge base, ensuring AI responses are grounded in your actual data rather than general knowledge. This dramatically improves accuracy and reduces hallucinations.
  </p>

